  <exercise id="fs-id1348247" type="ap-test-prep">
  <problem id="fs-id1618085">
  <para id="fs-id1512694">Tom has two pendulums with him. Pendulum 1 has a ball of mass 0.1 kg attached to it and has a length of 5 m. Pendulum 2 has a ball of mass 0.5 kg attached to a string of length 1 m. How does mass of the ball affect the frequency of the pendulum? Which pendulum will have a higher frequency and why?</para>
  </problem>
  <!--<solution id="fs-id1929583">
  <para id="fs-id1271400">The mass of the ball of the pendulum will not affect the period; hence it will not affect the frequency of the pendulum. Only the length of the pendulum matters. Pendulum 2 will have higher frequency as it has a shorter string. A shorter string oscillates with smaller period and hence will have higher frequency.</para>
  </solution>-->
  </exercise>
